First make sure that your React-Select options is an array of objects and contains, at minimum, a value and label property for each option, like so:

        [
            {value:&#39;value1&#39;, label:&#39;label1&#39;, otherProperty:&#39;otherProperty1&#39;},
            {value:&#39;value2&#39;, label:&#39;label2&#39;, otherProperty:&#39;otherProperty2&#39;}
        ]

To do so (assuming that `PatientApiService.fetchCaregivers()` returns an array of caregivers) create a renderOptions method:

    renderOptions=(options)=&gt;{
        return options.map(option=&gt;{
            return {value: option.idCaregiver , label:option.caregiverName}
        })
    }

Next keep in mind: &quot;React-Select&quot; does not return a typical event object such as: 

    {target:{value:&#39;value&#39; , label:&#39;label&#39; , name:&#39;name&#39;}}

Instead it returns whatever you passed in as an option to the options prop such as:

    {value:&#39;value&#39; , label:&#39;label&#39;}

